        <div class="container">
           <h2>Welcome {{ .Username }}.</h2>
	   <p class="lead">
           In order to get command-line access to the Kubernetes cluster, you will need to configure OpenID Connect (OIDC) authenication for your client.
       </p>
	   <p>
       Please follow <a href="https://code.uacf.io/projects/INFRA/repos/kubernetes/browse/docs/USER_README.md"> this </a> documentation for getting setup to connect to our Kubernetes clusters
       
       </p>
           <p class="lead">
	       Once kubectl is installed and setup, you may execute the following:
           </p>
           <pre class="bash">
$ kubectl config set-credentials self  \
    --auth-provider=oidc  \
    --auth-provider-arg=idp-issuer-url={{ .IssuerURL }}  \
    --auth-provider-arg=client-id={{ .ClientID }}  \
    --auth-provider-arg=client-secret={{ .ClientSecret }} \
    --auth-provider-arg=refresh-token={{ .RefreshToken }} \
    --auth-provider-arg=id-token={{ .IDToken }}
           </pre>
           <p>
           If you are trying to login to the kubernetes-dashboard you just need the following token
           </p>
           <pre class="bash">
{{ .IDToken }}
           </pre>
           </p>
        </div>
